Reading special texts, writing summaries and essays, making oral presentations, and developing listening skills. The course involves extensive reading in one's speciality. Grammar is revised in accordance with the students' needs.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop professional terminology and practical language skills in professional English.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the student1) knows the main terms from the speciality-relevant terminology; 2) can describe and analyze the main field-relevant issues in English; 3) can discuss the field-relevant issues both in Estonian and European context; 4) can make a presentation on a speciality-relevant topic.
